HEADWORD: Piña cloth
<hw>Pi"⟦ntil⟧a cloth`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[See
<er>Pi⟦ntil⟧a</er>.]</ety> <def>A fine fabric for scarfs, handkerchiefs,
embroidery, etc., woven from the fiber obtained from the leaf of the
sterile pineapple plant. It is delicate, soft, and transparent, with a
tinge of pale yellow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinacoid</ent>⟦br⟧
